  "soap_summary": "Patient with known heart failure presents with progressive shortness of breath over weeks, worse in last few days, with mild dry cough and new bilateral ankle swelling. No current chest pain or fever. Medications: furosemide, aspirin, statin, candesartan (metoprolol recently stopped). Plan: increase furosemide (short course increase to two tablets/day / one tablet twice daily), arrange blood tests (CBC, renal function) and echocardiogram, review in ~1 week or sooner if worsening.",
